    <title>Adding an IP Address to a Data Interface</title>
    <shortdesc>You can add IP addresses to a data interface using the web
        administration interface or the command line.</shortdesc>
    <prolog><author/>
        <author/>
    </prolog>
    <taskbody>
        <context id="context_N10022_N1001F_N10001">
            <draft-comment author="jowens">US62814 new topic</draft-comment>
            <p>For VXLAN connectivity between VMs, you must add appropriate endpoint
                IP addresses to the compute node interfaces.</p>
            <p>To add an IP address using the web administration interface, refer to the following
                steps. To use the command-line interface; see <xref href="jow1425584170078.xml"/>
            </p>
        </context>
        <prereq id="prereq_N1001F_N1001C_N10001">
            <p>To make interface changes, you must lock the compute host first.</p>
        </prereq>
        <steps id="steps_zkx_d1h_hr">
            <step id="step_N1003C_N10038_N1001F_N10001">
                <cmd>Lock the compute host.</cmd>
            </step>
            <step id="step_N10045_N10038_N1001F_N10001">
                <cmd>Set the interface to support an IPv4 or IPv6 address, or both. </cmd>
                <!-- These substeps are based on memory, since I can't find a lab I can use. -->
                <substeps id="substeps_erl_dgm_lt">
                    <substep>
                        <cmd>On the <uicontrol>Admin</uicontrol> menu, click
                                <uicontrol>Inventory</uicontrol> to open the <wintitle>System
                                Inventory</wintitle> page.</cmd>
                    </substep>
                    <substep>
                        <cmd>Select the <uicontrol>Host</uicontrol> tab, and then double-click the
                            compute host to open the <wintitle>Host Detail</wintitle> page.</cmd>
                    </substep>
                    <substep>
                        <cmd>Click <uicontrol>Edit Interface</uicontrol> for the data interface you
                            want to edit.</cmd>
                    </substep>
                    <substep>
                        <cmd>In the <wintitle>Edit Interface</wintitle> dialog box, set the
                                <uicontrol>IPv4 Addressing Mode</uicontrol> or the <uicontrol>IPv6
                                Addressing Mode</uicontrol> to
                            <nameliteral>Static</nameliteral>.</cmd>
                        <info>
                            <fig id="fig_ckc_dhm_lt">
                                <image href="jow1443040379028.image" id="image_xdf_phm_lt">
                                    <alt>TiS Edit Interface, IPv4 Static</alt>
                                </image>
                            </fig>
                        </info>
                    </substep>
                </substeps>
            </step>
            <step id="step_N100C0_N10038_N1001F_N10001">
                <cmd>Add an IPv4 or IPv6 address to the interface.</cmd>
                <substeps id="substeps_sp1_43m_lt">
                    <substep>
                        <cmd>On the <wintitle>Inventory Detail</wintitle> page, click the
                                <uicontrol>Name</uicontrol> of the interface to open the
                                <wintitle>Interface Detail</wintitle> page.</cmd>
                        <info>
                            <fig id="fig_a4y_bjm_lt">
                                <image href="jow1443041105867.image" id="image_jjh_cjm_lt">
                                    <alt>TiS Interface Detail page</alt>
                                </image>
                            </fig>
                        </info>
                    </substep>
                    <substep>
                        <cmd>Click <uicontrol>Create Address</uicontrol> to open the
                                <wintitle>Create Address</wintitle> dialog box.</cmd>
                        <info>
                            <fig id="fig_c33_xjm_lt">
                                <image href="jow1442607685238.image" id="image_rf4_bkm_lt">
                                    <alt>TiS Create Address</alt>
                                </image>
                            </fig>
                        </info>
                    </substep>
                    <substep>
                        <cmd>Enter the IPv4 or IPv6 address and netmask (for example,
                            192.168.1.3/24), and then click <uicontrol>Create
                            Address</uicontrol>.
                        </cmd>
                    </substep>
                </substeps>
                <stepresult>
                    <p>The new address is added to the <nameliteral>Address List</nameliteral>.</p>
                </stepresult>
            </step>
            <step id="step_N10152_N10038_N1001F_N10001">
                <cmd>Unlock the compute node and wait for it to become available.</cmd>
            </step>
        </steps>
    </taskbody>
</task-wr>